  "Remediation": "Problematic certificates need to be revoked and re-issued. Children certificates must also be re-issued. Expired certificates should also be purged from trusted certificates stores. When issuing certificates, the following requirements should be met: Use RSA or ECDSA for certificate signature (don't use DSA), RSA key length is equal to or greater than 2048 and an up-to-date library is used to generate the RSA key.",
